{"bookId": "67656cf0a790fd9b172cf0d2","moduleId": "67656cf0a790fd9b172cf0d2","subjectId": "67656cf8a790fd9b172cf0d3","chapterId": "67656cf8a790fd9b172cf0da","subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","count": 6,"questions": [{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<p>A rod <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mi>D</mi></math>&nbsp;of thermal resistance <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><msup><mi>KW</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math> is joined at the middle of an identical rod&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp;as shown in figure. The ends <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>B</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>D</mi></math> are maintained at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>200</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>,</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>125</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> respectively. The heat current in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mi>D</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi></math>. The value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> is</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1544a09e-7baa-42f9-b738-66dcf6a19bbf-image.png\" style=\"width: 321px; height: 224px;\" /></p>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p>&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mrow><mi>A</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mrow><mi>D</mi><mi>C</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>Q</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>200</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mfrac><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>125</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>&#8467;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>100</mn><mo>)</mo><mi>K</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow><mfrac><mi>&#8467;</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfrac></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>400</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>125</mn><mo>-</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>200</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>725</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>t</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>145</mn><mo>&#186;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>Q</mi><mrow><mi>C</mi><mi>D</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>A</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>145</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>125</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>&#8467;</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mfrac><mi>&#8467;</mi><mrow><mi>K</mi><mi>A</mi></mrow></mfrac></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">W</mi></math></p>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6b417cc3fb48d6752c","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "Starting at temperature <math><mn>300</mn><mi></mi><mi>K</mi><mo>,</mo></math> one mole of an ideal diatomic gas <math><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mi>&#947;</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1.4</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> is first compressed adiabatically from volume <math><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></math> to <math><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>.</mo></math> It is then allowed to expand isobarically to volume <math><mn>2</mn><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></math> . If all the processes are the quasi-static then the final temperature of the gas (in <math><msup><mrow><mi></mi></mrow><mrow><mi>o</mi></mrow></msup><mi>K</mi></math> ) is (to the nearest integer) ___________.","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<math><mi>P</mi><msup><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>y</mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></math><br /><math><mi>T</mi><msup><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">s</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">a</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">t</mi></math><br /><math><mn>300</mn><mi></mi><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>1.4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mi></mi><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math><br />Now for BC process<br /><math><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi></mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mi></mi><mfrac><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>v</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>8</mn><mo>/</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1818.859</mn></math><br /><math><msub><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1819</mn><mi></mi><mi>K</mi></math><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fefec39d-c84f-42af-b368-089e652d4f11.jpeg\" />","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a69417cc3fb48d66dd8","paperSource": "JEE Main 2020 (09 Jan Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<p>One mole of an ideal gas at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>27</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> is taken from <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> as shown in the given <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi></math> indicator diagram. The work done by the system will be _______&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>.</mo></math>&nbsp;[Given,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>mole</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6931</mn></math>] (Round off to the nearest integer)</p><p>(Round off to the nearest integer)</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ed0a09f8-b185-4bbb-965c-cf5ebc80fb78-image.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 230px;\" /></p>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p>Process of isothermal</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>T</mi><mi>&#8467;</mi><mi>n</mi><mfenced><mfrac><msub><mi>V</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>V</mi></mrow><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></mfenced></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>300</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mi>ln</mi><mn>2</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>17258</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p>","difficulty": "Easy","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6a417cc3fb48d670f9","paperSource": "JEE Main 2021 (20 Jul Shift 2)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<p>A unit scale is to be prepared whose length does not change with temperature and remains <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math>, using a bimetallic strip made of brass and iron each of different length. The length of both components would change in such a way that difference between their lengths remains constant. If length of brass is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>40</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math> and length of iron will be _____&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cm</mi></math>.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced close=\"\"><mrow><msub><mi>&#945;</mi><mrow><mi>iron</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced open=\"\"><mrow><msub><mi>&#945;</mi><mrow><mi>brass</mi><mo>&#160;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mrow><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<blockquote><p>Linear expansion of solid with temperature is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>L</mi><mi>f</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>L</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>&#945;</mi><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>T</mi></mrow></mfenced></math></p><p>Here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>&#945;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mi>&#916;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></msub><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>&#945;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></msub><mi>&#916;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>&#945;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></msub><msub><mi>&#945;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></msub></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>40</mn><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></msub><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>40</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn></math></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8658;</mo><msub><mi>l</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cm</mi></math></p></blockquote>","difficulty": "Hard","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6c417cc3fb48d677fe","paperSource": "JEE Main 2022 (25 Jul Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "<p>A steam engine intakes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi></math>&nbsp;of steam at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math> per minute and cools it down to <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn><mo>&#176;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>. If latent heat of vaporization of steam is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>540</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cal</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, then the heat rejected by the steam engine per minute is _____&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cal</mi></math></p><p>(Given : specific heat capacity of water : <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cal</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">g</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><msup><mmultiscripts><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mprescripts></mprescripts><none></none><mo>&#8728;</mo></mmultiscripts><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>)</p>","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<p>Heat rejected by the steam engine per minute will be equal to latent heat per minute plus heat rejected by the water to cool down.</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>H</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>L</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi>s</mi><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>T</mi><mspace linebreak=\"newline\"></mspace><mo>&#8658;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>H</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>&#8710;</mo><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>540</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>50</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><mn>80</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>31000</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cal</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>min</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>31</mn><mo>&#215;</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>cal</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><msup><mi>min</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math></p>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6c417cc3fb48d678b2","paperSource": "JEE Main 2022 (25 Jun Shift 1)"},{"id": 0,"subject": "Physics","chapter": "Thermodynamics","exam": "Engineering","examName": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","q": "At a certain temperature, the degrees of freedom per molecule for gas is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>. The gas performs <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>150</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math> of work when it expands under constant pressure. The amount of heat absorbed by the gas will be _____&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>.","options": ["A","B","C","D"],"answer": 0,"solution": "<blockquote><p>For constant pressure process,</p><p>Work done is given by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>W</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>&#916;</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>150</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math>, here,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi></math>&nbsp;is gas constant.</p><p>Now, for above process,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>.</p><p>So, specific heat at constant pressure is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mi>R</mi></math>.</p><p>Amount of heat adsorbed by the gas is&nbsp;</p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Q</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>n</mi><msub><mi>C</mi><mi>P</mi></msub><mi>R</mi><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>f</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mi>n</mi><mi>R</mi><mi>&#916;</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>150</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>750</mn><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">J</mi></math></p></blockquote>","difficulty": "Medium","source": "Top 100 Numerical Qs of JEE Main 2023-2020","_marksId": "648b5a6d417cc3fb48d67c90","paperSource": "JEE Main 2022 (28 Jul Shift 2)"}]}